My book knowledge ran out at 8...Nc6.  I know that is poor on my part with an opening I play so often but I do not enjoy studying the openings....I prefer getting right to the middle game and looking for tactics.  As it turns out, this move is still in book.  My analysis told me this loses a pawn but I went with it anyway due to seeing great activity for my army at the end of it.  I have been studying the difference between analysis and evaluation.  Analysis is calculating the material left after all the possible lines while evaluation is looking at the position after the captures are over.  Analysis put me down a pawn but evaluation gives compensation for the pawn.  Here is what I saw.....10. Nxd5 Nxd5 11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. exd5 cxd5 13. Qxd5.....nets a pawn for white.
